name: MarisBarney Garcia
text: Wynner, i guess if it's a matter of meeting basic needs (traffic, Bataan, etc) vs honor (LNMB issue), talaga namang the former that takes precedence. Diba nga, Maslow? Given the struggle to stay alive plus the rule of law, i get why many aren't AS concerned about labels to take to the streets (it doesn't strike me as complacency). And that's perfectly valid! Just as valid as how honor and heroism are valued by many. Stalemate nga. But at least both sides want to make things better.
